{"lemma":"ضِلْعِ","slug":"ضِلْعِ","root":"ض.ل.ع","root_slug":"ض-ل-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ل-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25955","","n25959","n25960","n25961","n25962","n25963"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to side"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cooperate, to make common cause"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be strong, to be robust, to be sturdy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to curve, to be bent","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bend, to (cause to) curve","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stripe, to make have streaks"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَلَعَ (ḍalaʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"affection, attachment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sympathy","examples":[{"text":"ضَلْعُهُ مَعهُ","english":"he sympathizes with him"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rib"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cutlet, chop"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side (of a triangle)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"post, banister (of a balustrade)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَلِعَ (ḍaliʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"ض ل ع (ḍ l ʕ)?\n\nCompare Aramaic אלעא (el‘ā, el‘o, “rib”) and Hebrew צֵלׇע (tselá', “rib”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25955","headword_ar":"ضَلَعَ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEN","text_ar":"ضَلْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he, inclined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he, declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviated, from that which was right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted wrongfully, unjustly, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa Eanohu","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deviated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned away, from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so, acting wrongfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted wrongfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEuka maEa fulaAnK","text_ar":"ضَلْعُكَ مَعَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, * K *) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy inclining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is with such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in unison with that of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, Msb, * K: * in the Msb and K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEahu","text_ar":"مَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa","text_ar":"مَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tanoqu$i Al$~awokapa biAl$~awokapi faA_in~a DaloEahaA","text_ar":"لَا تَنْقُشِ الشَّوْكَةَ بِالشَّوْكَةِ فَاـِنَّ ضَلْعَهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEahaA","text_ar":"مَعَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimivolihaA","text_ar":"بِمِثْلِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAl$wkp","text_ar":"بالشوكة"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Meyd,) [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Extract not thou the thorn by means of the thorn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of the like of it, for its inclination is with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning, demand not aid, in the case of thy want, of him who is more benevolent to the person from whom the object of want is sought than he is to thee: (Meyd:) a prov.: (S, Meyd, O:) applied to the man who contends in an altercation with another, and says, “ Appoint thou between me and thee such a one; ” pointing to a man who loves what he [i. e. the opponent of the speaker] loves: (S, O, K:) the author of the K adds, it is said that it should by rule be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEaka","text_ar":"ضَلَعَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEa maEa","text_ar":"ضَلِعَ مَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa","text_ar":"فَرِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inclined with such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but they have contracted it; which is wonderful, in consideration with his having mentioned shortly before,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa","text_ar":"مَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAla","text_ar":"مَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaASamotu","text_ar":"خَاصَمْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA fakaAna DaloEuka EalaY~a","text_ar":"فُلَانًا فَكَانَ ضَلْعُكَ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I contended in an altercation with such a one and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy inclining"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was against me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEa","text_ar":"ضَلِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEN","text_ar":"ضَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sword, K, or a thing, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tDl~E","text_ar":"تضلّع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean the same: (Ham p. 80:) a poet says, (namely, Mohammad Ibn-'Abd-Allah El-Azdee, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waqado yaHomilu Als~ayofa Almujar~aba rab~uhu\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY DalaEK fiY matonihi wahowa qaATiEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often, its owner bears the tried sword, notwithstanding crookedness in its broad side, it being sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) and (K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEN","text_ar":"ضَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved, by nature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEN","text_ar":"ضَلْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^uqiyman~a DalaEaka","text_ar":"لَاُقِيمَنَّ ضَلَعَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEaka","text_ar":"ضَلْعَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly straighten thy natural crookedness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) thus in the copies of the K; but this is a mistake, occasioned by the author's seeing in the T and M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^uqiyman~a DalaEaka","text_ar":"لَاُقِيمَنَّ ضَلَعَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaEaka","text_ar":"صَلَعَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawajaka","text_ar":"عَوَجَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and his imagining both these nouns to be with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to differ in the manner stated above: (TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEa","text_ar":"ضَلِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEN","text_ar":"ضَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved, by nature:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEN","text_ar":"ضَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the camel is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gamozN","text_ar":"غَمْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in horses or the like, [meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a slight lameness, in the hind leg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEa","text_ar":"ضَلِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the epithet [or part. n.] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEN","text_ar":"ضَلِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or this is rather the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEN","text_ar":"ضَلْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [or as Mtr says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloE","text_ar":"ضَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning what resembles"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarajN","text_ar":"عَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or natural lameness] is correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaloE","text_ar":"ظَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) but when it (i. e. the crookedness, TA) is not natural, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa","text_ar":"مَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [but this seems rather to relate to the meaning of “ limping, ” agreeably with what I have cited above from the Mgh,] and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEN","text_ar":"ضَلْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the epithet [or part. n.] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAliEN","text_ar":"ضَالِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaluEa","text_ar":"ضَلُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAEapN","text_ar":"ضَلَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, O, Msb, [and app. also a horse and the like, see its part. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliyEN","text_ar":"ضَلِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"powerful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong, hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firm, in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDolaAE","text_ar":"اَضْلَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ribs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K. [The latter is said in Har p. 6 to be the primary meaning; and the former, metaphorical.])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDal~aEa","text_ar":"تَضَلَّعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEa fulaAnFA","text_ar":"ضَلَعَ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck such a one upon his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaE","text_ar":"ضِلَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rib"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Meyd","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25959","headword_ar":"ضَلْعٌ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25960","headword_ar":"ضِلْعٌ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first and last sentences."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25961","headword_ar":"ضَلَعٌ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of debt,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that bends the bearer thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, Msb, K;) a subst. in this sense, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaluEa","text_ar":"ضَلُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endurance of that which is heavy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burdensome."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  Also inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliEa","text_ar":"ضَلِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Mgh, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25962","headword_ar":"ضَلِعٌ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved, by nature."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) And applied to a spear as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved; not straightened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 80:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaliyEN","text_ar":"ضَلِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAliEN","text_ar":"ضَالِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so applied,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1800},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 1, in the last quarter of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25963","headword_ar":"ضِلَعٌ","root":"DlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiloEN","text_ar":"ضِلْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) the former of the dial. of El-Hijáz and the latter of the dial. of Temeem, (Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaloEN","text_ar":"ضَلْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the only form, or almost the only one, that is used by the vulgar, is said by MF to be mentioned by some one or more of the commentators, but not known in the lexicons, (TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rib;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain appertenance of an animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved thing of the side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single bone of the bones of the side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) of the fem. gender, (Msb, K, TA,) accord. to common repute; or, as some say, masc.; or, accord. to some, whose opinion in this case is preferred by Ibn-Málik and others, of both genders: (TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuluwEN","text_ar":"ضُلُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDolaAEN","text_ar":"اَضْلَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoluEN","text_ar":"اَضْلُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaAliEu","text_ar":"اَضَالِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as some say, of [its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoluEN","text_ar":"اَضْلُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEu Alxalofi","text_ar":"ضِلَعُ الخَلْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxilofi","text_ar":"الخِلْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rib"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lowest part of the side"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a man, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lowest rib;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hindmost rib"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a beast]: (TA:) and signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A burn in the part behind what is thus termed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN","text_ar":"عُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [erroneously supposed by Golius and Freytag to mean here the musical instrument thus called;] (IAar, O, K;) so in a saying of the Prophet to a woman, respecting a blood-stain on a garment,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hut~iyhi biDilaEK","text_ar":"حُتِّيهِ بِضِلَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Scrape thou it off with a piece of stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, O:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is wide and curved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaE","text_ar":"ضِلَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) of an animal. (K.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oblong piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a melon; (O, * K, TA;) as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaE","text_ar":"ضِلَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly thus called]. (O, TA.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A trap"},{"kind":"text","text":"for birds; because of its gibbous shape: so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaba DilaEFA lilT~ayori","text_ar":"نَصَبَ ضِلَعًا لِلطَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set up a trap for the birds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower part, of a raceme of a palm-tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ehn","text_ar":"عهن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A line that is made on the ground, after which another line is made, and then the space between these two is sown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small mountain apart from others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small mountain, such as is not long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a low and narrow mountain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Nasr, S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long and extended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to As,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small mountain, extending lengthwise upon the earth, not high."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuluwEN","text_ar":"ضُلُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Curved tracts of ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracks"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iq","text_ar":"طَرَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of stony ground such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~ap","text_ar":"حَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K, TA.) ―         -b8-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An island in the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDolaAEN","text_ar":"اَضْلَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, as some say, it is the name of a particular island. (TA.) ―         -b9-  [In geometry, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a rectilinear triangle or square or polygon. ―         -b10-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A square root;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called in arithmetic"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*orN","text_ar":"جَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end of the paragraph.] ―         -b11-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo EalaY~a","text_ar":"هُمْ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN jaAy^irapN","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ جَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, O, K, in the last of which, between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hm","text_ar":"هم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY~","text_ar":"علىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is inserted"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiloEN","text_ar":"ضِلْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is allowable, (S, TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are assembled against me with hostility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) the origin of which is the saying of AZ, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo EalaY~N A_ilobN waAHidN","text_ar":"هُمْ عَلَىٌّ اـِلْبٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobN waAHidN","text_ar":"اَلْبٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN waAHidN","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN waAHidN","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning as above. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","IAar","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}